		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://www.caw599.ca/?p=652</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[Your Bargaining Committee unanimously recommends acceptance of the Tentative Agreement reached between Xstrata Copper Canada and the unionize employees at their Kidd Metallurgical Site dated October 5th, 2008.
Cost of Living Adjustment (COLA) of $0.75 will be rolled into the base rate
Wages – 3.25 %, 3.0%, 2% + COLA
Example for a current Code 5 P&#38;M Employee:
$26.53 [...]]]></description>
			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p id="top" />Your Bargaining Committee unanimously recommends acceptance of the Tentative Agreement reached between Xstrata Copper Canada and the unionize employees at their Kidd Metallurgical Site dated October 5th, 2008.</p>
<p>Cost of Living Adjustment (COLA) of $0.75 will be rolled into the base rate</p>
<p>Wages – 3.25 %, 3.0%, 2% + COLA</p>
<p>Example for a current Code 5 P&amp;M Employee:</p>
<p>$26.53 add $0.75 COLA adjustment = $27.28<br />
$27.28 x 3.25% = $28.17 effective October 1st, 2008<br />
$28.17 x 3.00% = $29.02 effective October 1st, 2009<br />
$29.02 x 2.00% = $29.60 effective October 1st, 2010 plus COLA</p>
<p>Total wage increase at Code 5 equals $1.43 per hour plus 2008 COLA roll-in of $0.75 for a total of $2.18 per hour, not including projected cost of living increases in the third year of the contract</p>
<p>Signing Bonus - $2,000</p>
<p>Shift Premiums - 	10 hour shift workers will be paid $0.55/hour after 4:00 PM,<br />
an increase of 15 cents per hour</p>
<p>12 hour shift workers will be paid $0.65/hour after 4:00 PM,<br />
an increase of 20 cents per hour</p>
<p>Family Day has been added to the agreement</p>
<p>Local Education Fund will be increased by 3 cents/hour worked</p>
<p>Apprentices will receive a $500 Tool Allowance over the life of the agreement and their time away at trade school will no longer be held against them for vacation credits and annual production/productivity bonuses. Previously agreed upon SUB Plan agreements remain in place and the Joint Apprenticeship Committee will make recommendations to the Company regarding any previous experience</p>
<p><strong>Dental Plan</strong></p>
<p>There will now only be a two year lag based on the ODA Rates in effect January<br />
1st, 2009.</p>
<p><strong>Vision Care Plan</strong></p>
<p>Increased from $250 every two years to $325 every two years which includes eye exams</p>
<p><strong>Extended Health Benefits</strong></p>
<p>Elimination of $300 cap per service with overall paramedical maximum of $1,000/person/year</p>
<p>Medical Form reimbursement increased from $10 to $25</p>
<p>The Company will allow the union representatives access to Medical Insurance Carriers in order to help resolve issues regarding our members’ claims for benefits</p>
<p>The Company has committed to cooperate with the full-time worker Health and Safety representative in providing required information in a timely manner</p>
<p>If an employee’s contributory portion of any benefit plan is in arrears due to his or her time off the job for an extended period of time due to illness or injury, repayments can be arranged on a reasonable schedule</p>
<p>The Company will allow Banked Time to be rolled over between contracts</p>
<p>Disciplinary suspensions now have a 36 month sunset clause and cannot be held against them instead of staying in the employee’s file indefinitely</p>
<p>The Company has agreed that the Joint Disability Management Committee will have input when any Job Posting requirements include medical assessments</p>
<p>Return to Work Protocol:</p>
<ul>
<li>No one will lose vacation days, seniority or credits for production/productivity bonuses for time off the job while on strike</li>
<li>No one will be laid off or demoted as part of the Return to Work Agreement</li>
<li>Employees will return to work only after being notified by the Company</li>
<li>No member will stay at home while a contractor does their job</li>
<li>No one will be discharged as a result of any pre-strike or strike activity</li>
<li>Outstanding grievances have been dealt with</li>
</ul>
]]></content:encoded>
