			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p id="top" /><strong>CAW Local 599 and Xstrata Copper Reach an Agreement</strong></p>
<p><strong>Timmins, On – November 6th, 2008</strong></p>
<p>CAW Local 599 has ratified a 3 year agreement with Xstrata Copper Canada at their Kidd Metallurgical Site in Timmins.</p>
<p>77% of the membership attended the meeting this afternoon and voted 77% in favour of accepting the contract that had been recommended unanimously by their Bargaining Committee.</p>
<p>Significant gains were made in wages, benefits and contract language. A $2,000 signing<br />
bonus was also bargained for the striking workers who have been on the picket line since October 1st.</p>
<p>After rolling in the $0.75 per hour cost of living adjustment into the base rate of pay, members will receive an additional wage increase of 3.25% in the first year, 3.0% in the second year and 2% plus another cost of living adjustment in year three.</p>
<p>“The Bargaining Committee wishes to thank its members for the solidarity they have displayed during our 5 week struggle with Xstrata” said the union local’s Chairperson Ben Lefebvre. “Hopefully the company will finally get the message that our members will not be taken advantage of and that they are prepared to do whatever it takes to get the dignity and respect we all deserve from this multi-national corporation”.</p>
]]></content:encoded>
