			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p id="top" /><strong>Timmins, On – November 5th, 2008</strong></p>
<p>CAW Local 599 and Xstrata Copper Canada have reached a tentative agreement after two days of bargaining.</p>
<p>A ratification meeting with the union membership is scheduled for 12 noon on November 6th at the McIntyre Community Center in Schumacher.</p>
<p>The Union Bargaining Committee is unanimously recommending acceptance of their tentative agreement.</p>
<p>CAW Local 599 represents 675 Production and Maintenance workers at Xstrata’s Kidd Metallurgical Site in Timmins. They have been on strike against their employer since October 1st.</p>
