			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p id="top" />
<h2>Highlights of Agreement between Steel and Goldcorp</h2>
<p>Wage increase of 12% over three year contract</p>
<p>Improved contracting out language</p>
<p>Recall rights moved to 36 months</p>
<p>Reporting Pay to ½ shift from 4 hours</p>
<p>Added son and daughter in law to Bereavement Leave clause</p>
<p>Short Term Disability moved to $600 from $550</p>
<p>Company will pay $35 for each insurance application form</p>
<p>Extended Benefit Coverage for dental, drugs and vision to 3 months in case of lay-off and dependent coverage for up to 2 years in case of member’s death</p>
<p>Prescription glasses to $325 from $300 every 24 months</p>
<p>Dental Fee Schedule (ODA rates) to remain current in each year of the contract</p>
<p>Training Premium of $2.00 per hour</p>
<p>Night shift premium to $0.80 per hour</p>
<p>Severance pay to 2 weeks per year of service</p>
<p>Your Bargaining Committee will return to negotiate with Xstrata on November 4th without pre-conditions in order to reach a collective agreement that respects the interests of our members and their families.</p>
<p>I do not expect to achieve everything listed above nor do I expect us to win every issue we now have before the Company, even though I believe them to be exactly what our members want and truly deserve.</p>
<p>I commit to try to bargain the best agreement possible on your behalf and in the end, it will be up to the membership to decide if what is offered by Xstrata is accepted or rejected. We will always do what our members think is right considering all the circumstances.</p>
<p>Ben Lefebvre</p>
]]></content:encoded>
