			<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p id="top" /><strong>BISSON WANTS MINISTER TO KEEP ONTC AWAY FROM XSTRATA STRIKE</strong></p>
<p><strong>QUEEN’S PARK</strong>—After questioning from Timmins-James Bay MPP Gilles Bisson last week, today Northern Development Minister Michael Gravelle said ONTC employees or equipment will no longer cross the Xstrata Mine picket line in Timmins.</p>
<p>During today’s Question Period, Bisson wanted assurances that this won’t happen again. <em>“The Minister says it won’t happen again but we will be monitoring the situation. We have word the ONTC is lending equipment to Xstrata so they can move their trains.”</em></p>
<p>Last week Bisson was upset to learn the ONTC crossed the picket line. He became more upset learning that the Minister claimed to have no knowledge of the incident. <em>“That’s a pretty scary thought, that the minister who’s responsible for the Ontario Northland Transportation Commission (ONTC) and ultimately the ONR was not aware that his managers crossed the picket line in order to train the management at Xstrata to run the rail system that runs ore from the mine to the metallurgical site.”</em></p>
<p>Bisson says the McGuinty Government must tell the ONTC to stay out of the area and allow the employees and the company to resolve their differences.  <em>“No staff or equipment of the crown should be on that site…period.”</em></p>
]]></content:encoded>
